§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A ❬trigonometric polynomial❭ of order $n$ is a function $u:
    𝗥 → 𝗥$ for which there exists $α_0, α_1, …, α_n, β_1, β_2,
    …, β_n ∈ 𝗥$ so that
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ u(x) = α_0 + ∑_{k = 1}^{n} \parens*{α_k \cos(kx) + β_k
        \sin(kx)}. ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ In other words,
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \begin{aligned} ⦉

      ‖ u(x) = α_0 +& α_1\cos x + β_1\sin x + α_2 \cos2x +
        β_2 \sin2x + ᜶ &·s + α_n \cos nx + β_n \sin nx. ⦉

      ‖ \end{aligned} ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

